
                                            Only vehicles with parking tickets will be allowed through the check points on Nasrec Road, Soweto Highway, Randshow Road and the N17.

                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) are diverting traffic around the FNB Stadium ahead of Soweto derby between Orlando Pirates and Kaizer Chiefs this afternoon. Only vehicles with parking tickets will be allowed through the check points on Nasrec Road, Soweto Highway, Randshow Road and the N17. Motorists are advised to use alternative routes to avoid traffic congestion. JMPD’s Wayne Minnaar said, “There is road diversion around the FNB Stadium for the derby. Motorists can use alternative routes and the diversion will be lifted at 7pm.”